REGEX EXPLANATION:
Before: /^[\+]?[\(]?[0-9]{1,4}[\)]?[-\s\./0-9]*$/
After:  /^[+]?[(]?[0-9]{1,4}[)]?[-\s./0-9]*$/
- [+]? : optional plus sign
- [(]? : optional opening parenthesis
- [0-9]{1,4} : 1-4 digits (country code)
- [)]? : optional closing parenthesis
- [-\s./0-9]* : zero or more separators or digits

SECURITY NOTE:
The control character removal in sanitizeInput() is intentional for security:
- Prevents null byte injection: \x00
- Removes control chars that could break terminals/logs: \x01-\x1F
- Preserves legitimate whitespace: \x09 (tab), \x0A (LF), \x0D (CR)

